 labium, lateral view; (E), right labial palp, ventrolateral view; (F), right labial palp, dorsolateral view. All scale bars represent 0.5 mm. Arrows indicate protuberance." captionText-3="FIGURE 6. Mouthparts of Indocnemis orang larva. (A), left mandible, ventral view; (B), left mandible, ventrointernal view; (C), left mandible, dorsal view; (D), left mandible, ectal view; (E), right mandible, dorsal view; (F), right mandible, internal view; (G), right mandible, ventral view; (H), right mandible, ectal view; dorsal view; (I), maxilla, dorsal view; (J), maxilla, internal view; (K), maxilla, lateral view; (L), maxilla, ventral view. All scale bars represent 0.5 mm." captionText-4="FIGURE 7. Thoraxes and legs of Indocnemis orang larva. (A), thorax, dorsal view; (B), thorax, lateral view; (C), ventral view; (D), foreleg; (E), midleg; (F), hindleg; (G), tibial comb. Scale bars for G represents 0.5 mm; A, B, C represent 1 mm; D, E, F represent 2 mm." captionText-5="FIGURE 8. Gonapophysis of Indocnemis orang larva. (A), male gonapophysis, ventral view; (B), male gonapophysis, lateral view; (C), female gonapophysis, ventral view; (D), female gonapophysis, lateral view. All scale bars represent 1 mm." captionText-6="FIGURE 9. S9–10 of Indocnemis orang larva, removed of caudal gills. (A–C), male; (D–F), female; (A, D), Posterior view; (B–E), dorsoposterior view; (C–F), lateral view. All scale bars represent 1 mm." captionText-7="FIGURE 10. Caudal gills of Indocnemis orang larva. (A), median gill; (B), lateral gill; (C), enlarge of serrated teeth on dorsal of median gill; (D), enlarge of serrated teeth on ventral of median gill; (E), enlarge of serrated teeth on ventral of lateral gill; (D), enlarge of serrated teeth on dorsal of lateral gill. All scale bars represent 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541705" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541707" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541709" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541711" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541714" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541716" figureDoi-6="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541718" figureDoi-7="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541720" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6541705/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6541707/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6541709/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6541711/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6541714/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/6541716/files/figure.png" httpUri-6="https://zenodo.org/record/6541718/files/figure.png" httpUri-7="https://zenodo.org/record/6541720/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="506">
Figures 3– 
<geoCoordinate id="7BB45060FFF89E097E41FF59095C3A87" box="[281,310,187,213]" degrees="10, 12" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="506" precision="555" value="10.12">10</geoCoordinate>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="86BB2A22FFF89E097E1AFF59091F3A87" box="[322,373,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="11.[151,250,870,894]" captionTargetBox="[178,1425,284,762]" captionTargetId="figure-465@11.[151,1436,257,783]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 12. Schematic contour of ligula (median lobe of prementum) of Asian representative Platycnemididae larvae: (A), poorly produced ligula; (B), moderately produced ligula; (C), strongly produced ligula; (D), Nososticta moluccensis redrawn from Lieftinck (1953); (E), Prodasineura autumnalis redrawn from Lieftinck (1953); (F), Copera chantaburii redrawn from Saetung et al. (2020); (G), Pseudocopera ciliata redrawn from Saetung et al. (2020); (H), Caconeura gomphoides redrawn from Fraser (1943); (I), Platycnemis echigoana redrawn from Eda (1965); (J), Onychargia atrocyana redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2015b); (K), Calicnemia gulinensis redrawn from Chen &amp; Yu (2020); (L), Coeliccia flavostriata redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2016); (M), Disparoneura apicalis redrawn from Fraser (1943); (N), Indocnemis orang, this study." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541724/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="506">12N</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="86BB2A22FFF89E097ED8FF5909DB3A87" box="[384,433,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1632,1656]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,189,1607]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[151,1436,181,1608]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 13. Drawing of median gill of larva of representatives of Asian Platycnemididae: (A), Calicnemia gulinensis,redrawn from Chen &amp; Yu (2020); (B), Disparoneura apicalis, dorsal view, redrawn from Fraser (1943); (C), Nososticta moluccensis, redrawn from Lieftinck (1953); (D), Coeliccia flavostriata, redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2016); (E), Coeliccia campioni, redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2016); (F), Caconeura gomphoides, redrawn from Fraser (1943); (G), Onychargia atrocyana, redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2015b); (H), Indocnemis orang, this study; (I), Copera chantaburii, redrawn from Saetung et al. (2020); (J), Coeliccia cyanomelas, redrawn from Xu (2013); (K), Prodasineura autumnalis, redrawn from Lieftinck (1953); (L), Platycnemis echigoana redrawn from Ishida (1996); (M), Pseudocopera ciliata redrawn from Saetung et al. (2020). Arrows indicate nodus of caudal gills." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541726/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="506">13H</figureCitation>
